document_data.History:
It was said that many celadrins could trace their origin back to the height of [[Myth Drannor]], a time of liberation and understanding. After the fall of Myth Drannor, celadrins moved to [[Deepingdale]] and [[Lake Sember]]. They also originated from other communities with prominent temples to Hanali Celanil, such as [[Evermeet]] and [[Evereska]].

The [[Church of the Winsome Rose]] had celadrin warlocks among its defenders. In the late 14{{th}} century [[DR]], at least three had became [[eldritch theurge]]s, who tried to restore love among elven races in Cormanthor.

During the same time period, one celadrin was also known to be a member of the [[Kaliesh'erai]], a [[psionic]] elven organization located in [[Evereska]].{{Cite web/Class Chronicles: Psionics Across the Land}}
